page.title: 14A Day in my Life
page.content: I live in Aston on Carrant in the country. When I wake up in the morning I can hear the birds and I sometimes hear a cuckoo. Then my mum comes and wakes me up. When I have washed, daddy who hasn't gone to work yet often sees the race horses gallop along the field.There's a lot of panic in the mornings but when we get to school mummy says goodbye.At school we do lots of writing and maths.At school we can have either school dinners or sandwiches. I have sandwiches and go on second sitting.When I get home I go up to my bedroom and watch the rabbits and I sometimes see some pheasants.My house is very big and I have a very big garden.I have a racer bike and go haring around the garden with my sister Nicole.There is a lorry depot called Warner's up our lane but it is still very peaceful.
